Inventory File - Add the below two lines in the end of the file
$ sudo vi /etc/ansible/hosts 
[localhost]
local

Then save the file and come out of it.

Now execute the ansible playbook by using a command
$ ansible-playbook terminate_ec2.yaml -e ec2_id=i-xxxx
$ ansible-playbook terminate_ec2.yaml -e ec2_id=i-xxxx,i-xxxx

LINK
https://www.cidevops.com/2018/03/terminate-ec2-ansible-playbook-example.html
